    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">Why Sprinklers Break Down Here</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Las Cruces is one of the hardest environments in the country on irrigation equipment. The UV exposure is relentless — plastic heads, risers, and valve diaphragms degrade faster here than anywhere with milder sun. Add hard water that deposits minerals inside nozzles and screens, and freeze-thaw cycles that crack fittings from November through March, and most sprinkler systems in Las Cruces need some level of repair every few years.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Builder-grade systems are especially vulnerable. Developers typically install the cheapest components with minimal zone design. Within a few years, you get dead zones, overspray onto hardscape, and valves that stick open and waste water. It's the single most common repair call we get.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">David has been diagnosing and repairing sprinkler systems across Las Cruces for over 19 years. He works on every brand, every system type, and he'll give you an honest assessment — if it's worth fixing, he'll fix it right. If replacement makes more sense, he'll tell you that too.</p>
